headline: ADP National Employment Report Preliminary Estimate for February 7, 2026
summary: For the four weeks ending February 7, 2026, U.S. private employers added an average of 12,750 jobs per week, according to the NER Pulse, a weekly update of the monthly ADP National Employment Report (NER).

headline: The One Money Move Everyone Should Make as Layoffs Grow
summary: With U.S. layoffs seeing rises lately, job security may be shaky. See the outlook and the one savings move, building an emergency fund, that can help.
